# Seatly — Cursor Rules
# Read this entire file before writing any code

## Project Overview
Seatly is a multi-restaurant CRM and booking platform.
Web app: Next.js + Tailwind CSS
Mobile app: Expo SDK 52 + React Native
Backend: Supabase + Edge Functions + Claude API

## Before Every Session
1. Read BACKEND.md — know what tables exist before touching anything
2. Read CHECKLIST.md — never rebuild something already done
3. Use Plan mode — always show a plan and wait for approval
4. Reference the nearest existing screen as a template for new screens

## Database Rules — Non-Negotiable
NEVER create a new Supabase table that is not in BACKEND.md
NEVER add a column that is not documented in BACKEND.md
NEVER modify or delete an existing table
NEVER disable Row Level Security on any table
NEVER suggest disabling RLS to fix a bug — find the real fix
If a screen needs something not in BACKEND.md, STOP and tell
the developer instead of creating it yourself

## Security Rules — Non-Negotiable
NEVER hardcode API keys, passwords, or secrets in any file
ALL secrets must use environment variables (process.env.VARIABLE)
NEVER commit .env files — they are in .gitignore
NEVER use NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix for secret keys
NEVER expose the Supabase service role key to the frontend

## Design Rules — Non-Negotiable
NEVER hardcode hex colour values anywhere in the codebase
NEVER hardcode pixel values, spacing numbers, or font sizes
ALL colours must be imported from packages/tokens
ALL spacing must be imported from packages/tokens
ALL font sizes must be imported from packages/tokens
If a value is not in the tokens file, ask before creating it

## Code Rules
TypeScript only — no .js or .jsx files
Functional components only — no class components
Named exports only — no default exports for components
Always handle three states on every screen:
  - Loading state (data is being fetched)
  - Empty state (no data exists yet)
  - Error state (something went wrong)
Never use inline styles — always use Tailwind classes (web)
  or StyleSheet.create with token values (mobile)

## AI Rules — Non-Negotiable
Claude API is for conversation, suggestions, and natural
language queries ONLY
NEVER send financial calculations to the Claude API
NEVER send tax calculations to the Claude API
NEVER let Claude API write directly to the database
ALL money calculations happen in PostgreSQL and Edge Functions
Claude API calls go through Supabase Edge Functions only
Never call the Claude API directly from the frontend

## Multi-Restaurant Rules
Every database query MUST filter by restaurant_id
A restaurant can NEVER see another restaurant's data
Always verify RLS is enforcing restaurant isolation
Never query a table without a restaurant_id filter

## New Screens Rule
When creating a new screen:
1. Check BACKEND.md — confirm all tables needed exist
2. Copy the structure from the nearest existing screen
3. Never start from a blank component
4. Apply the correct role permission for this screen
5. Import all values from packages/tokens

## UI DESIGN RULES — MANDATORY FOR EVERY SCREEN

### Theme
- Dark mode only — never use light backgrounds
- Black and gold — Apple Mac sleek minimal
- Every screen must feel premium and consistent
- Reference UI_STYLE_GUIDE.md for all values

### Backgrounds
- Main screen background: backgroundDark (#0A0A0A)
- Cards and panels: surfaceDark (#141414)
- Elevated elements (modals, dropdowns): surfaceDarkElevated (#1A1A1A)
- Inputs: surfaceDark (#141414)
- Never use white, grey, or any light colour as a background

### Typography
- Headings: font-bold or font-semibold, tight letter spacing
- Body: text-base, leading-relaxed
- Labels and captions: text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-gold
- Never use more than 2 font weights on a single screen

### Colours
- All colours from packages/tokens only
- Never hardcode any hex value
- Gold is used on: active states, CTAs, key metrics, brand elements, focus rings
- Gold is NOT used on: body text, backgrounds, regular borders

### Buttons
- Primary: bg-gold text-text-on-gold rounded-md font-semibold hover:bg-gold-muted
- Secondary: border border-gold text-gold hover:bg-gold/10
- Destructive: bg-error text-white
- All buttons: hover:scale-[1.02] transition-transform duration-400

### Inputs
- Background: bg-surface-dark
- Border: border-border-dark
- Focus: focus:border-gold focus:ring-1 focus:ring-gold
- Text: text-text-on-dark
- Placeholder: text-text-muted-on-dark
- Border radius: rounded-md

### Cards
- Background: bg-surface-dark
- Border: border border-border-card
- Border radius: rounded-lg
- Padding: p-xl
- Hover: hover:border-gold/50 hover:shadow-gold-glow-hover

### Navigation (Web Sidebar)
- Active item: border-l-2 border-gold bg-gold/10 text-gold font-medium
- Inactive item: text-text-muted-on-dark
- Hover: hover:bg-gold/5 hover:text-text-on-dark

### Badges and Status
- VIP badge: gold border and text
- Allergy badge: error colour, always visible
- Status pills: rounded-full with appropriate status colour

### Spacing
- All spacing from packages/tokens only
- Screen padding: px-xl py-2xl
- Card padding: p-xl
- Between sections: gap-2xl or gap-3xl
- Between elements: gap-md or gap-lg

### Every Screen Must Have
- Loading state (spinner or skeleton)
- Empty state (icon, message, optional CTA)
- Error state (message, retry button)
- All three states use tokens, not custom colours

### Animations
- Transitions: duration-400 ease-out
- Hover effects: scale-[1.02] on buttons
- Page entry: fadeInUp with Intersection Observer
- Never use jarring or fast animations

### Allergy Alerts — Special Rule
- Allergies are ALWAYS shown in error colour
- Never muted, never hidden, always visible
- This applies to every screen where guest data is shown

### Mobile Specific (Expo)
- Import from packages/tokens/theme.native.ts
- Never hardcode values in StyleSheet.create
- Status bar: always light
- Safe area: always respected
- Tab bar: dark background, gold active icon

### Web Specific (Next.js)
- Import from packages/tokens
- Tailwind classes only — no inline styles
- No hardcoded values in className strings
